data: {"title": "Structural Mechanics", "credits": 3, "credit_type": "ECTS", "parent_code": "HVVK.01.178", "lecturer": "Leele V\u00e4lja", "Curricula": [{"curriculum_title": "Estonian Native Craft"}], "type": "Regular course", "study_levels": [{"en": "professional higher education studies"}], "hours": {"lecture": 30, "practice": 0, "seminar": 0, "colloquium": 0, "web_learning": 0, "individual_work": 0, "internship": 0}, "prerequisites": [{"required": true, "title": "Mathematics", "credits": 3}], "independent_work_assessments": [{"work_type": "final written assessment", "description": {}}], "study_languages": [{"en": "Estonian"}], "description": "Theoretical mechanics - statics: main definitions and theorems. Newton's laws, force in engineering, couple of forces, torque, the principle of independence of forces, two-dimensional force system, equilibrium equations, the equilibrium of a body in the circumstances of a friction. Basic terminology of the theory of elasticity of the strength of materials: stress; internal force, external force, Hooke's law, deformation, surface moments, stability of a rod subjected to compression. Statics-determined beams, support reactions, diagrams of internal forces (bending moment, shear force, axial force).", "objectives": [{"en": "Provide students with general knowledge of linear structural elements, the internal forces in linear structural elements caused by external forces, methods for determination, and determination of the load-bearing capacity of such structures."}], "learning_outcomes": [{"en": "Upon successful completion of the course students:"}, {"en": "-\tcan prepare a framework (calculation scheme) for a real structure;"}, {"en": "-\tcan determine the level of statical indeterminacy of the structure;"}, {"en": "-\tcan determine the support reactions and internal forces caused by external forces that influence the framework;"}, {"en": "-\tcan determine the characteristics of the cross-sections of the bars of the framework;"}, {"en": "-\tcan determine the strength and stability of the framework."}], "part": "part 2", "structural_unit": "Viljandi Culture Academy"}

growth, finding and overcoming personal limitations, planning a personal learning process, effective time management for learning, emotion management, coping with stress, and burnout prevention.", "objectives": [{"en": "The aim of the course is to support students' self-directed  learning process, help participants to acknowledge their strengths and limitations, and acquire necessary {"title": "International Trade: Theory and Empirics", "credits": 6, "credit_type": "ECTS", "parent_code": "MJJV.07.100", "lecturer": "Priit Vahter", "Curricula": [{"curriculum_title": "Quantitative Economics"}], "type": "Regular course", "study_levels": [{"en": "master's studies"}], "hours": {"lecture": 40, "practice": 0, "seminar": 6, "individual_work": 0, "internship": 0}, "independent_work_assessments": [{"work_type": "final written assessment", "description": {}}], "study_languages": [{"en": "English"}], "description": "This course gives an in-depth overview about the classical and contemporary theory of international trade, theory of trade policy, and their applications.", "objectives": [{"en": "The aim of the course is to deepen the knowledge of students about theory of international trade, theory of trade policy, and their applications.   We will use both the theories of perfectly competitive and imperfectly competitive markets, depending on particular trade models. Recent developments in the areas of trade theory and trade empirics will be discussed."}], "learning_outcomes": [{"en": "Students acquire following skills and knowledge:"}, {"en": "* Knowledge of main theories of international trade, an advanced core field of economics"}, {"en": "* Skills to apply mathematical, statistical and econometric methods in analysis of international trade and trade policy"}, {"en": "* Ability to critically evaluate empirical studies in the field of international trade"}, {"en": "* Knowledge about developments in the field of international trade and application of trade policy in the world"}], "part": "None", "structural_unit": "Chair of International Business and Innovation"}

{"title": "Painting", "credits": 1.5, "credit_type": "ECTS", "parent_code": "P2VK.04.652", "lecturer": "Kersti Rattus", "Curricula": [{"curriculum_title": "Performing Arts"}, {"curriculum_title": "Theatre Technical Arts"}], "type": "Regular course", "study_levels": [{"en": "professional higher education studies"}], "hours": {"lecture": 0, "practice": 24, "seminar": 0, "colloquium": 0, "web_learning": 0, "individual_work": 0, "internship": 0}, "independent_work_assessments": [{"work_type": "practical assignment", "description": {}}], "study_languages": [{"en": "Estonian"}, {"en": "English"}], "description": "Painting still lives in warm, cold and neutral colors. Presenting shapes by light and shades. Analysis of light and shade on the basis of still life in similar light shades. Color circle, different types of harmony, contrasting colors. Preparations for painting in nature, reproduction of landscape painting.", "objectives": [{"en": "To create the conditions for learning the laws of depicting nature and to
use them in creative self expression. To be able to use water colors on the
necessary level for professional use."}], "learning_outcomes": [{"en": "Upon successful completion of the course students:
- can see and understand the color qualities, shades, color palette,
lightness and darkness, saturation, air perspective, the tonal
relationships of light and shade of the surrounding environment and items.

- know and use the principles of creating a scenic whole with the help of
color scheme according to the needs of the specialty

- have mastered the water color technique according to the needs of the
specialty

- can motivate themselves independently and know how to properly present
their work

   - can independently analyze and evaluate their work process and its
   outcome
   - use the terms learned in the study in their analysis"}], "part": "part 4", "structural_unit": "Viljandi Culture Academy"}
